reviewText: Very good course.
Good

The course unfolds with the basic building blocks of the Post-Keynesian perspective of an economy. The level of instruction is appropriate for beginners until concepts are woven together in Unit 4. The pace of the lecture combined with the "tying together" of concepts raises the level well above the beginner level. Overall, I enjoyed the course and the lively instructor!

Lo acabo de tomar como un preambulo a una proxima asignatura de macroeconomia en mi universidad. Espero que lo disfruten!
